B136 — DUSKHALLOW LOOT TABLES & DROP LOGIC (LV 40–49)
1. Duskhollow Loot Identity

Duskhollow is the first zone where loot feels truly dangerous and weird.

Design goals:

Themed around:

Shadow, void, curses, life-drain

Ambush, stealth, CC

Clear reward fantasies:

AGI players hunt stalkers/howlers for Umbrafang leather.

Tanks go after constructs/wards for Dreadbulwark heavy.

Casters chase witches/phantoms for Riftbound cloth.

Materials shift toward:

Nightroot, Gloomshard, Voidglass, Rift-Touched Essence.

Baseline per kill:

Coin roll (always).

Material roll.

Equipment roll (Uncommon / Rare).

Special roll (ultra / zone world drops).

2. Core Duskhollow Enemies (Lv 40–49)

Covered here:

Gloomling Creeper

Nightroot Howler

Umbral Stalker

Gloamscour Witch

Rift-Torn Construct

Shadowgrasp Horror

Nightroot Entangler

Moonless Stag (rare spawn)

Riftwound Shade (rare spawn)

Shade Sovereign (zone elite / boss)

You can bind these to whatever exact NPC names you already have; this is the mechanical identity.

2.1 Gloomling Creeper (Lv 40–43, Insect / Spider)

Role: Poison/slow spider-type in the underbrush.
Fantasy: “Poison mats, early Duskhollow Uncommons for all three archetypes.”

Common Drops

Coin:

40–70 copper.

Materials (95% total):

1–3 × Gloomling Venom Sac

1–3 × Duskhollow Silk

Junk:

Cracked Gloom Carapace (vendor junk).

Uncommon Equipment (~18% per kill)

One of:

Gloomstep Stalker’s Bracers (Leather Wrist, Uncommon 40)

Hollow Warden’s Vambraces (Heavy Wrist, Uncommon 40)

Gloomweaver’s Wraps (Cloth Wrist, Uncommon 40)

Roughly ~6% each.

Rare Pool (~2.0% total)

One of:

Umbrafang Stalker’s Bracers (Rare 46)

Dreadbulwark Vambraces (Rare 46)

Riftbound Wraps (Rare 46)

These are the entry-point rares for each armor type.

2.2 Nightroot Howler (Lv 41–45, Beast)

Role: Fast pack-hound, stacked bleed or fear howl.
Fantasy: “AGI/STA leather, rings and early Rare boots.”

Common Drops

Coin:

42–78 copper.

Materials:

1–3 × Nightroot Pelt

0–2 × Howler Fang

Uncommon Equipment (~20% total)

One of:

Gloomstep Stalker’s Hood (Leather Head, Uncommon 41)

Gloomstep Stalker’s Treads (Leather Feet, Uncommon 40)

Umbrafang Tracker’s Seal (AGI ring, Uncommon 42)

Rare Pool (~3.0% total)

One of:

Umbrafang Stalker’s Treads (Rare 46)

Umbrafang Shadeband (Rare 47 ring)

Ultra-Rare (~0.2% total)

Nighthowl Collar

Rare+/Legendary trinket: AGI/STA, small crit, plus minor movespeed at night or in Duskhollow.

2.3 Umbral Stalker (Lv 43–47, Humanoid / Beast)

Role: Stealth assassin-type; backstab, silence, escape.
Fantasy: “High-end AGI loot, serious hunter/rogue focus.”

Common Drops

Coin:

50–90 copper.

Materials:

1–3 × Umbral Hide Strip

0–2 × Void-Soaked Claw

Uncommon Equipment (~22% total)

One of:

Gloomstep Stalker’s Jerkin (Leather Chest, Uncommon 41)

Gloomstep Stalker’s Legwraps (Leather Legs, Uncommon 42)

Nightroot Hunter’s Pendant (Neck, Uncommon 42)

Rare Pool (~4.0% total)

One of:

Umbrafang Stalker’s Hood (Rare 47)

Umbrafang Stalker’s Legwraps (Rare 48)

Gloomshard Recurve (Rare 48 bow)

Umbrafang Fangblade (Rare 49 dagger)

Ultra-Rare (~0.25% total)

Umbral Fangring

Legendary-ish ring: AGI/STA, crit, small chance for attacks from stealth/openers to deal bonus shadow damage.

2.4 Gloamscour Witch (Lv 42–48, Caster Humanoid)

Role: Void/curse caster, shadow bolts, fear, curses.
Fantasy: “Top-tier caster cloth and trinkets for this band.”

Common Drops

Coin:

52–96 copper.

Materials:

1–3 × Witch’s Shadowfloss

0–2 × Void-Touched Residue

Uncommon Equipment (~24% total)

One of:

Gloomweaver’s Cowl (Cloth Head, Uncommon 41)

Gloomweaver’s Robe (Cloth Chest, Uncommon 41)

Voidglass Focus Stone (Trinket, Uncommon 43)

Duskgloom Wand (Wand, Uncommon 43)

Rare Pool (~5.0% total)

One of:

Riftbound Hood (Rare 47)

Riftbound Robe (Rare 47)

Rift-torn Channeling Staff (Rare 48 staff)

Gloamscour Hexwand (Rare 48 wand)

Duskhollow Luminary’s Sigil (Rare 47 ring)

Ultra-Rare (~0.35% total)

Witch-Queen’s Eye

Legendary trinket: INT/SPI/SP, small spellcrit, chance on spell hit to briefly reduce target’s shadow resistance or increase shadow damage taken.

2.5 Rift-Torn Construct (Lv 44–48, Construct)

Role: Heavy-hitting void construct; slow, hard to kill.
Fantasy: “Tank/DPS plate and big weapons, plus void-flavored mats.”

Common Drops

Coin:

56–100 copper.

Materials:

1–3 × Rift-Forged Shard

0–2 × Voidglass Fragment

Uncommon Equipment (~24% total)

One of:

Hollow Warden’s Chestguard (Heavy Chest, Uncommon 41)

Hollow Warden’s Legplates (Heavy Legs, Uncommon 42)

Shadowbastion Mace (Uncommon 43 1H mace)

Hollowguard Shield (Uncommon 43 shield)

Rare Pool (~5.0% total)

One of:

Dreadbulwark Chestguard (Rare 47)

Dreadbulwark Legplates (Rare 48)

Riftforged Warhammer (Rare 48 1H mace)

Umbral Wall (Rare 48 shield)

Ultra-Rare (~0.4% total)

Riftheart Bulwark

Legendary shield: strong STA/STR, armor, block chance, plus a small chance when blocking to apply a short-duration damage debuff on attacker.

2.6 Shadowgrasp Horror (Lv 45–49, Aberration)

Role: Tentacled void horror, pulls and fears, big threat.
Fantasy: “Top-end off-hands, rings, and strange hybrid gear.”

Common Drops

Coin:

60–110 copper.

Materials:

1–3 × Shadowgrasp Tendril

0–2 × Eldritch Ichor

Uncommon Equipment (~22% total)

One of:

Duskhollow Wardstone Medallion (STR tank neck, Uncommon 42)

Nightroot Channeler’s Pendant (INT/SPI neck, Uncommon 42)

Umbrafang Tracker’s Seal (AGI ring, Uncommon 42)

Rare Pool (~4.5% total)

One of:

Umbrafang Huntlord’s Pendant (Rare 48)

Dreadbulwark Signet (Rare 47 tank ring)

Duskhollow Luminary’s Sigil (Rare 47 caster ring)

Ultra-Rare (~0.35% total)

Grasp of the Deep Rift

Legendary ring: primary stat + STA, good defensive sub-stat, plus small chance on being hit to apply a minor movement slow to attacker.

2.7 Nightroot Entangler (Lv 40–44, Plant / Vine)

Role: Roots, slows; low mobility but high control.
Fantasy: “Support/profession mats and mid-level slot fillers.”

Common Drops

Coin:

38–68 copper.

Materials:

1–3 × Nightroot Tendril

0–2 × Entangling Spores

Uncommon Equipment (~16% total)

One of:

Gloomweaver’s Sash (Cloth Waist, Uncommon 41)

Gloomstep Stalker’s Belt (Leather Waist, Uncommon 41)

Hollow Warden’s Girdle (Heavy Waist, Uncommon 41)

Rare Pool (~2.5% total)

One of:

Riftbound Sash (Rare 47)

Umbrafang Stalker’s Belt (Rare 47)

Dreadbulwark Girdle (Rare 47)

2.8 Moonless Stag (Lv 44–47, Rare Spawn Beast)

Role: Quiet rare roaming under dark sky phases.
Fantasy: “Single-target prize for people who actually explore/don’t grind only.”

Common Drops

Coin:

60–100 copper.

Materials:

1–3 × Moonless Antler Shard

0–2 × Gloam-Infused Hide

Rare Pool (~40% on kill, rare spawn)

One of:

Umbrafang Shadeband (Rare AGI ring 47)

Dreadbulwark Signet (Rare STR ring 47)

Duskhollow Luminary’s Sigil (Rare INT ring 47)

Ultra-Rare (~1.0% total)

Moonless Mantle

Legendary cloak: hybrid stats, small dodge/avoid, slight movespeed at night.

2.9 Riftwound Shade (Lv 46–49, Rare Spirit)

Role: Teleporting, phase-shifting rare; high burst magic damage.
Fantasy: “Caster/burst loot, high-identity drop.”

Common Drops

Coin:

70–120 copper.

Materials:

1–3 × Riftwound Essence

0–2 × Shattered Voidglass

Rare Pool (~45% on kill, rare spawn)

One of:

Riftbound Hood (Rare 47)

Riftbound Legwraps (Rare 48)

Gloamscour Hexwand (Rare 48 wand)

Ultra-Rare (~1.0% total)

Riftwound Circlet

Legendary head: high INT/SP, good spirit, small periodic chance to cause your next spell to be instant cast (with long internal cooldown).

2.10 Shade Sovereign (Lv 49, Zone Elite / Boss)

Role: The apex of Duskhollow; shadow/void boss.
Fantasy: “This is the capstone for the 40–49 band. Players expect real loot.”

Guaranteed Drops

Coin:

2.0–3.0 silver.

Materials:

3–6 × Sovereign Shadowcore

2–4 × Rift-Touched Essence

1–2 × Nightroot Heartwood

Uncommon Equipment (100%: 1–2 items)

Random from:

Any Gloomstep Stalker Uncommon piece

Any Hollow Warden Uncommon piece

Any Gloomweaver Uncommon piece

Voidglass Focus Stone

Rare Pool (80%: 1 item)

One of:

Umbrafang Stalker’s Jerkin (Rare 47 chest)

Dreadbulwark Chestguard (Rare 47 chest)

Riftbound Robe (Rare 47 chest)

Gloomshard Recurve (Rare 48 bow)

Riftforged Warhammer (Rare 48 1H mace)

Rift-torn Channeling Staff (Rare 48 staff)

Ultra-Rare (~0.6% total)

Sovereign’s Shadowcore

Legendary crafting core used in high-end recipes beyond 49.

Optionally also:

One random Duskhollow world-drop legendary (see next section).

3. Duskhollow World Drop Table (Lv 40–49)

All non-critter mobs in Duskhollow, Lv 40–49, roll a small bonus chance at this table after their normal loot.

Suggested rates:

Normal mobs: ~0.05% per kill.

Elites / rares: 0.15–0.4% per kill.

Candidate world-drops (all slightly above regular Rare power):

Gloamthread Drape (Back)

AGI/INT hybrid, STA, +1% dodge or spell avoid, minor shadow resist.

Umbral Signet (Ring)

Primary stat, STA, +1% crit, small shadow damage bonus.

Riftglass Talisman (Neck)

INT/SPI, SP, small spellcrit, minor mana-per-5.

Nightroot Fangblade (Dagger)

AGI/STA/AP, 2% crit, small on-hit shadow proc with ICD.

You can later promote some of these into the global “uniques/legendaries” B-block for higher polish, but mechanically they live here.

4. Lua Loot Table Examples (Duskhollow)

These follow the same structure as Greatwood / Ashen Ridge / Frostmarch.

local function LootEntry(itemId, chance, minCount, maxCount)
    return {
        itemId   = itemId,
        chance   = chance,
        minCount = minCount or 1,
        maxCount = maxCount or minCount or 1,
    }
end

LootTables = LootTables or {}

-- Gloomling Creeper
LootTables["Duskhollow.GloomlingCreeper"] = {
    coin = { min = 40, max = 70 },

    materials = {
        LootEntry("MAT_GLOOMLING_VENOM_SAC",  0.85, 1, 3),
        LootEntry("MAT_DUSKHALLOW_SILK",      0.75, 1, 3),
    },

    junk = {
        LootEntry("JUNK_CRACKED_GLOOM_CARAPACE", 0.40, 1, 1),
    },

    equipment = {
        -- Uncommon
        LootEntry("ITEM_GLOOMSTEP_STALKERS_BRACERS",  0.06, 1, 1),
        LootEntry("ITEM_HOLLOW_WARDENS_VAMBRACES",    0.06, 1, 1),
        LootEntry("ITEM_GLOOMWEAVERS_WRAPS",          0.06, 1, 1),

        -- Rare
        LootEntry("ITEM_UMBRAFANG_STALKERS_BRACERS",  0.0065, 1, 1),
        LootEntry("ITEM_DREADBULWARK_VAMBRACES",      0.0065, 1, 1),
        LootEntry("ITEM_RIFTBOUND_WRAPS",             0.0065, 1, 1),
    },

    worldDrop = {
        LootEntry("ITEM_GLOAMTHREAD_DRAPE", 1.0, 1, 1),
    },
}

-- Shade Sovereign
LootTables["Duskhollow.ShadeSovereign"] = {
    coin = { min = 200, max = 300 },

    materials = {
        LootEntry("MAT_SOVEREIGN_SHADOWCORE", 0.95, 3, 6),
        LootEntry("MAT_RIFT_TOUCHED_ESSENCE", 0.90, 2, 4),
        LootEntry("MAT_NIGHTROOT_HEARTWOOD",  0.70, 1, 2),
    },

    equipment = {
        -- Uncommon pool
        LootEntry("ITEM_GLOOMSTEP_STALKERS_JERKIN", 0.12, 1, 1),
        LootEntry("ITEM_HOLLOW_WARDENS_CHESTGUARD",0.12, 1, 1),
        LootEntry("ITEM_GLOOMWEAVERS_ROBE",        0.12, 1, 1),
        LootEntry("ITEM_VOIDGLASS_FOCUS_STONE",    0.08, 1, 1),

        -- Rare pool
        LootEntry("ITEM_UMBRAFANG_STALKERS_JERKIN", 0.13, 1, 1),
        LootEntry("ITEM_DREADBULWARK_CHESTGUARD",   0.13, 1, 1),
        LootEntry("ITEM_RIFTBOUND_ROBE",            0.13, 1, 1),
        LootEntry("ITEM_GLOOMSHARD_RECURVE",        0.09, 1, 1),
        LootEntry("ITEM_RIFTFORGED_WARHAMMER",      0.09, 1, 1),
        LootEntry("ITEM_RIFTTORN_CHANNELING_STAFF", 0.09, 1, 1),
    },

    ultra = {
        LootEntry("ITEM_SOVEREIGNS_SHADOWCORE", 0.006, 1, 1),
    },

    worldDrop = {
        LootEntry("ITEM_UMBRAL_SIGNET", 1.0, 1, 1),
    },
}


You can mirror this pattern for all remaining Duskhollow mobs by just swapping:

MAT_ ids for materials

ITEM_ ids for armor/weapons

Coin ranges and chances per role
